examples.en: The young woman was his confederate, of course.

examples.en: Canada decided to confederate and become a nation.

examples.en: The thief escaped, but his confederate was apprehended.

examples.en: The nations confederated in order to lower international trade barriers.

examples.en: The Confederate army was a vast grey.

examples.en: The Confederate side was prepared to attack.
The police were able to track down his confederates once the thief started talking.

examples.en: They styled their nation 'The Confederate States'.

examples.en: The Union and the Confederate accounts of the battle don't dovetail at all.
